div.span: A bubbler will be installed in the exhaust line immediately downstream of the vacuum pump and upstream of the fume hood. Its primary function is to act as a one-way valve, preventing backflow of atmospheric air and contaminants into the vacuum system. This ensures that the ALD chamber remains free from oxygen, moisture, and other impurities, thereby preserving the integrity of the thin film growth process.
